headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson scored 21 points and the Los Angeles Clippers got back on track with a 107-96 victory over the lowly Detroit Pistons on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 21 points, Clippers beat Pistons 107-96

headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. matched a career high with seven 3-pointers and had 27 points off the bench, helping the surging Charlotte Hornets snap the Minnesota Timberwolves’ five-game winning streak with a 133-115 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oubre, Hornets blister Timberwolves from long range, 133-115

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The Phoenix Suns are taking a 15-game winning streak to Brooklyn for a showdown with the Nets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Suns extend win streak to 15, beat Knicks 118-97

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 23 points, Zach LaVine added 21 and the Chicago Bulls beat the Orlando Magic 123-88 on a Friday night that belonged to Nikola Vucevic.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 23 points, Bulls rout Magic 123-88

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 23 points and 18 rebounds, and the Indiana Pacers beat the short-handed Toronto Raptors 114-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis powers balanced Pacers past short-handed Raptors

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 31 points and 10 assists to lead the Atlanta Hawks to a 132-100 victory Friday night over the Memphis Grizzlies, who lost star point guard Ja Morant to a left knee injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young leads Hawks past Grizzlies as Morant injures left knee

events.name: Washington Wizards at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Kentavious Caldwell-Pope scored a season-high 20 points, Bradley Beal also had 20 and the Washington Wizards beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 101-99 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Caldwell-Pope, Beal help Wizards beat Thunder, 101-99

events.name: Boston Celtics at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — San Antonio blew another big lead, but this time it led to a celebration for the Spurs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs best Celtics 96-88 after blowing 24-point advantage

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 24 points and 13 rebounds, Pat Connaughton added 20 points off the bench and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the depleted Denver Nuggets 120-109 on Friday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Nuggets 120-109, extend win streak to 6 games

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Devonte’ Graham made a go-ahead 3-pointer with 1.9 seconds to lift the New Orleans Pelicans to a 98-97 victory over the Utah Jazz on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham's 3-pointer lifts Pelicans to 98-97 win over Jazz

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry took a few minutes after another spectacular performance to return to the court and cheer up emotional teammate Klay Thompson when his Splash Brother needed some moral support.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 32 points as Warriors top Trail Blazers 118-103

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Alvin Gentry said when he became Sacramento's interim coach that it was going to take everyone if the Kings were going to stop their season from spiraling out of control.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Hield lead Kings over Lakers 141-137 in triple OT
